      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. it's a good start but i think my students need more specific, granular points. can you expand on the \"national sovereignty\" and \"rule of law\" parts? like, what are the actual philosophical or legal justifications they can use to argue that a nation has a moral right to strictly control who enters? i want them to have arguments that aren't just 'it's our border' but something more deep and principled.",
